u-Kama Public Glossary (Lossy Version)

u-Kama
A system that ties economic participation to ecological reality, so money serves continuity rather than extraction.

BIO (BioDollar)
The participation and coordination token used inside u-Kama. It enables access, contribution, and accountability. It is not marketed as a “green investment.”

BDR (Bio Dynamic Regeneration Record)
A long-term ecological record. It exists to constrain the system by remembering what endured in the land over time. It does not circulate like money.

Ecological Continuity
Nature holding its ground through time. If a defined state persists through a defined season of pressure, it counts. If it breaks, it does not.

Proof of Protection (PoP)
A record that a place stayed within agreed bounds through a defined period. It rewards restraint, not claims or activity.

Proof of Regeneration (PoR)
A record that a place measurably improved and the improvement held through time.

Seasons as Tests
u-Kama evaluates outcomes at seasonal endpoints, not on demand. Nature is judged on survival through cycles, not on paperwork.

Witnessing
Truth is recognised through independent observation and accountability over time. Effort and good intentions do not qualify on their own.

Cell
A defined area small enough that failure cannot be hidden and responsibility is clear.

Right of Use (ROU)
Recognised authority to steward land without owning it. It clarifies who may act and who must answer for outcomes.

Constraint First
Ecological truth does not “back” the token. Instead, ecological truth limits what the token may do.

Ecological Difficulty Adjustment
As ecosystems recover, proving continued improvement gets harder, slower, and stricter. Success tightens the system. It never loosens it.

No Offsetting Inside u-Kama
Failure in one place cannot be cancelled by success elsewhere. Each place must stand on its own.

Community as the Operating System
Local custodianship, legitimacy, and lived responsibility are the foundation. Technology supports this. It does not replace it.

What u-Kama is not
Not a carbon offset scheme.
Not a nature-backed stablecoin.
Not a market for “selling nature.”
Not a way to buy control through funding.

Core promise
u-Kama converts external demand for ecological continuity into protection capacity and custodial livelihoods, without turning nature into a financial product.